.ralph/runs/2026-07-09_141049_architecture_review/evidence/terminal-logs/codex.log:276:- `architecture-review`: independent quality review, run automatically by the loop every `architecture_review_every_completed_slices` slices. The reviewer does NOT modify production code. It must: (1) read the diffs of slices merged since the last review; (2) critique test quality — real assertions, edge cases, not just coverage numbers; (3) spot-check doc fidelity against the slice's source references and digests; (4) check for duplication and architecture drift; (5) write findings to `docs/working/REVIEW_FINDINGS.md` (append, newest first) and create or sharpen corrective slices for anything significant; (6) record ADRs for durable decisions; (7) spot-check that the functional-spec requirement IDs (M##-FR-###) of each epic completed since the last review are implemented or explicitly deferred in ASSUMPTIONS.md. This is the independent second pair of eyes on work where the same agent wrote both code and tests.
