docs/source/codebase-design.md:3316:- What is the module?
docs/source/codebase-design.md:3321:- Is the module deep or shallow?
docs/source/codebase-design.md:3337:- Views are thin.
docs/source/codebase-design.md:3338:- Serializers do not contain deep business logic.
docs/source/codebase-design.md:3360:- Feature modules are cohesive.
docs/source/codebase-design.md:3379:Build deep modules early enough that screens do not hardcode business logic.
docs/source/codebase-design.md:3405:1. Should the production deployment use one Django project with modular apps, or should any module be split into a separate service later?
docs/source/codebase-design.md:3437:The SFPCL platform should be implemented as a modular Django + React monorepo, but the most important design unit is the **module**, not the folder.
docs/source/codebase-design.md:3439:The deepest modules should own the most important SOP behaviour:
docs/source/codebase-design.md:3453:- Permission and Audit modules.
docs/source/codebase-design.md:3458:Do not let SOP complexity leak into views, serializers, React pages, reports or integrations. Put the complexity behind small, explicit module interfaces at clean seams, test through those interfaces, and use adapters only where behaviour truly varies.
docs/working/IMPLEMENTATION_SLICE_INDEX.md:3:This index is the ordered Ralph implementation queue. Broad module concepts live in `docs/epics/`; these slice files are the actual AFK work units.
