docs/working/ASSUMPTIONS.md:29:| A-025 | Communication send/list APIs use narrow permissions `communications.communication.read` and `communications.communication.send`, seeded to the existing Compliance owner role. Approved template effectiveness is evaluated against the server's current local date, and `merge_data` must exactly match `ContentTemplate.variables_json`: missing and extra keys both return `400 VALIDATION_ERROR` before any `Communication` or `AuditLog` write. | Source §39.2-§39.3 and §24.2 require communication APIs and snapshots, while `auth-permissions.md` still lacks exact §12 communication history/send codes and the source is silent on extra merge keys. Exact merge keys are the deterministic default for auditable rendered snapshots; broad document/config/report permissions are not reused. | `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §39.2-§39.3; `docs/source/data-model.md` §24.2; `docs/source/auth-permissions.md` communication/content-template risk notes; `docs/slices/003I-notification-adapter-shell.md` | 003I-notification-adapter-shell | Medium | Yes | 2026-07-06 | If source docs add a dedicated Communication role, exact §12 permission catalogue entries, timezone/effective-date semantics, or permissive merge-key handling, update the seed, service validation, tests, and this assumption. |
docs/working/ASSUMPTIONS.md:31:| A-027 | Background scheduling starts as a database-backed metadata shell (`scheduled_jobs`) and internal service boundary only. 003J does not add Celery/Redis, a worker process, public scheduler endpoints, scheduler administration permissions, dashboard task generation, notification generation, reminder cadence, report generation, or provider calls. Allowed job types are a conservative source-backed set for future report exports, notifications, reminders, interest accrual, DPD calculation, and compliance reminders. | Source roadmap names Redis/Celery for later notifications/jobs/reports and says silent job failures require job run records/alerts, but the slice explicitly forbids adding new scheduler dependencies unless already pinned/importable and forbids inventing reminder/report business rules. A local metadata table gives later slices an auditable foundation without external execution semantics. | `docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md` §10.3, §30.2, §31.1; `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §40.7-§40.8; `docs/slices/003J-background-job-scheduling-foundation.md` | 003J-background-job-scheduling-foundation and future async/reminder/report slices | Medium | Yes | 2026-07-07 | Future slices that add real workers, admin APIs, retry policies, job alerts, report export endpoints, reminder generation, or notification generation must confirm source-backed permissions, audit actions, and business timing/cadence before implementation. |
